title: Andheri Raat Mein Diya Tere Haath Mein
subTitle: Two friends join the underworld to make money and to lead a comfortable life. Later, they realise the ill-effects of crime and want to lead a normal life.

title: Ponga Pandit
subTitle: Two fathers make arrangements and marry their young children. However, years later when the nuptials are almost finalised, the girl rejects the boy.

title: Ek Musafir Ek Hasina
subTitle: A runaway bride meets a charming stranger and falls in love with him while tending to his wounds. However, when the man meets with an accident leading to amnesia, he completely forgets her.

title: My Life My Story
subTitle: The host invites prominent Bollywood celebrities who open up about their personal life and share interesting anecdotes based on their experiences.

title: Bhuvan Shome
subTitle: A lonely bureaucrat goes on holiday to a village in Gujarat where a young peasant woman helps him see beyond his job and develop a newfound empathy for people.

title: Purab Aur Pachhim
subTitle: Bharat, a freedom fighter's son, travels to England to study and strives to change the mindset of the people there towards India.

title: Apne Apne
subTitle: Ravi gets married to Sharda against his mother's wish. However, when Sharda suffers a miscarriage and leaves Ravi, he marries Seema, a rich woman.

title: Maang Bharo Sajana
subTitle: Chandra, a college student, loves Gita and wishes to marry her. When Gita's father discovers this, he rejects his proposal claiming that Chandra is not the biological son of his mother Sita.

title: Suraj
subTitle: King Vikram arranges his daughter Anuradha's match with his commander's son Pratap. However, trouble strikes when Anuradha is abducted by a bandit Suraj when she goes to attend Pratap's coronation.

title: Tyagi
subTitle: Shankar, a good man, takes the blame when one of his brothers is accused of a murder. However, when he returns from jail, he realises that his brothers are trying to create a rift in the family.

title: Indrajeet
subTitle: Indrajeet, a retired police officer, sets out to take revenge on his ex-lover's brother and friends for murdering his adopted daughter and son-in-law.

title: Indrajeet

title: Teri Maang Sitaron Se Bhar Doon
subTitle: Kamini pretends to be wealthy in front of her daughter, while living a contradictory reality. However, her life takes a surprising turn when her boss, an outlaw named Sultanbhai, comes to her rescue.

title: Chhota Bhai
subTitle: Annapurna is forced to look after her husband's young stepbrother Ramlal. She has her own child to look after but takes on Ramu's responsibility as well.

title: My Life My Story
subTitle: The host invites prominent Bollywood celebrities who open up about their personal life and share interesting anecdotes based on their experiences.

title: Pyar Kiye Jaa
subTitle: Ramlal, a widower, struggles to find suitable grooms for his daughters and to control his son's film obsession. To make matters worse, one of his former employees launches a protest against him.

title: Prem Kahani
subTitle: Rajesh, an apolitical poet, is in love with Kamini and leads a peaceful life. However, when his brother is killed by the British government, he decides to become a revolutionary and joins the freedom struggle.

title: The Emperor of the Mughals
subTitle: A storm brews inside the royal palace and threatens to swallow up the entire kingdom, as a Mughal emperor's pride clashes with the blossoming love between his son and a court dancer.

title: Bobby
subTitle: Raja, the son of a rich Hindu businessman, falls in love with Bobby, a poor Catholic girl. Though their families try to keep them away from each other, they strive to be together.

title: Do Raaste
subTitle: Navendu looks after his stepmother and half-brothers to fulfil the promise he has made to his father. However, their family falls apart after one of them marries a rich, controlling woman.

title: Saagar
subTitle: Raja secretly loves Mona, but she is in love with Ravi. However, Ravi's grandmother disapproves of their relationship and asks Mona to forget him and marry someone else.

title: Saagar

title: Rakta Bandhan
subTitle: Chandan is found dead by his twin brother Trishul, who is a dacoit. In a bid to turn a new leaf and leave the criminal life behind, Trishul assumes his brother's identity.

title: Baat Ban Jaye
subTitle: Nisha, a wealthy woman in charge of her family business, does not want to marry a rich man. She falls in love with Suraj Singh, a wedding singer and dancer, without realising that he has other plans.

title: Mome Ki Gudiya
subTitle: Ravi falls in love with Sheel but is shocked to learn that her marriage is fixed with his father. Even after his father steps back and Ravi gets married to Sheel, dark secrets loom over the newlyweds.

title: Shiv Sati Vivah
subTitle: Bringing the best in cinema.

title: Sheshnaag
subTitle: Pritam and Banu, two shape-shifting snakes in human form, seek protection from a young man when an evil priest tries to hunt them down and use them in a ritual for wealth and immortality.

title: Tum Haseen Main Jawaan
subTitle: Sunil, a navy officer, falls for Anuradha. However, things get complicated when Ranjeet, Anuradha's admirer, claims that she is a single mother.

title: Amrit
subTitle: A widowed man and woman face abuse from their respective children and seek comfort from each other instead.

title: Kohram
subTitle: When a teacher is killed by two village tyrants, Thakur and Kalia, his brother Arjun swears to avenge him. Years later, Arjun kills Thakur and then joins forces with his brother's sons to face Kalia.

title: Izzat
subTitle: Constable Ram Chandra teaches his son Siddharth to be a diligent policeman and lead his life with honesty and dignity. Siddharth follows his advice until circumstances force him to leave his ideals.

title: Chitchor
subTitle: When Geeta's sister arranges her wedding with a young engineer, their father mistakenly brings the wrong man home. However, as love blossoms between the two, the arrival of a letter startles everyone.
